pessulus: pessulus (GNOME Administrative Lockdown Configuration Editor)
pessulus:
pessulus: Pessulus is a lockdown editor for GNOME, written in python.  Pessulus 
pessulus: enables administrators to set mandatory settings in GConf affecting
pessulus: the configuration of the GNOME Desktop. The users can not change these 
pessulus: settings.  Use of pessulus can be useful on computers that are open 
pessulus: to use by everyone, e.g. in an internet cafe or a classroom, or even
pessulus: a home computer.
